{
  "stem": "4764.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Actually, the stove-- the old-fashioned type of stove, was lifted out and people went-- the floor-boards were removed and people hid in this cellar under the stove, or the entrance, which was under the stove.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were quite a few, so it must have been a sort of communal hiding place for particular people in this particular house that we were in, or this particular two-story place, because it was very crowded.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was very-- it was-- it happened very-- at odd times and very frequently, it seemed to me.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because all of a sudden, I was bundled out and told not to cry or utter a sound, whisked down into the kitchen, and hidden underneath.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my mother used to keep a little bit of chocolate, so she would bribe me with that, and I would eat that and not cry.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there were other little children there, too, and no one was allowed to cry.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the reason-- I remember distinctly-- was that the cry of a child used to give the hiding place away.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she used to tell me this, that-- that, you know, her friends whose child had cried, the Germans had come and picked them up and taken them away to the concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I was not allowed to utter a sound.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was very afraid, yes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think fear was my-- my sort first experience of life.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I assumed for many years that fear was a normal-- a normal state.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the sort of environment that we lived in I imagined was the whole world.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because, of course, a child at that age doesn't understand that there's something beyond the area where they're actually living.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I remember that I thought this was how the whole world existed.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
